{
  "article_id": "SanFranciscoChronicle1893_Jul8",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "The story from "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "must be taken with the same allowances as the reports of volcanic activity near the "
      },
      {
        "text": "mouth of the Colorado river",
        "entity_key": "re_coloradoriver",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Ignorant fishermen and sailors are easily alarmed by anything that has the appearance of the supernatural, and a heavy earthquake attended by changes in the familiar shore lines would be sufficient to spread fear. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "has never been held in favor with the Indians, which accounts for the fact that "
      },
      {
        "text": "the lost woman of San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was allowed to live on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the desolate spot",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "for nearly a half century. She, by the way, did not belong to the original inhabitants whose skulls so thickly fill the soil of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", but she had gone with her people from "
      },
      {
        "text": "the neighboring mainland",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "It was in transferring ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "this handful of Indians",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "to ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a reservation in Santa Barbara county",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "mi_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "that she was left on ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "where she led a Crusoe life for so many years.",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "She forgot her native speech and adopted some unintelligible gibberish, which probably gave rise to the legend that she was the last descendant of ",
        "tropes": [
          14,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the aborigines of the islands",
        "tropes": [
          14,
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          14,
          6
        ]
      }
    ]
  ]
}